The paper proposes a new online learning problem and algorithm, which is related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG), as well as data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm involves making decisions based on stochastic values, which is a common theme in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also evaluates the algorithm empirically, which is a common practice in machine learning and artificial intelligence research. Finally, the paper derives theoretical bounds on the algorithm's performance, which is related to mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
